name: Torii and Shrine
description:
A torii gate and shrine. Kyoto, Japan.

Torii gates are ubiquitous in Japan, as are the Shinto shrines behind them. Beautiful and varied in size and design, the torii establish a spiritual separation between the day-to-day world outside and the spiritual world of Shinto within.

You will find them everywhere, from busy city streets to serene parks and wilderness areas.
